quotas.tooltip_content: **Eligibility for the Quota : ACMS - Army Wards Quota** 1. The applicants must fall into one of the following categories 1. Children of serving Army personnel with minimum 10 years continuous service in the Army. 2. Children of Ex-Army personnel granted/awarded regular pension, family pension, liberalized family pension or disability pension at the time of their superannuation, demise, discharge or Release/Invalidment Medical Board. This includes children of recruits medically boarded out and granted disability pension. 3. Children of Ex-Army personnel who have taken discharge or been released aftert ten years of service. 2. Adopted/step children and children of remarried widows: 1. Adopted Children of Army personnel if adopted at least five years prior to seeking admission. 2. Step children are eligible, provided they are born from a wedding where at least one parent belonged to the Army and who is otherwise eligible. 3. Eligibility Criteria in Special Cases : 1. Children of Army Medical/Dental Corps Officers presently serving with Navy or Air Force who have served in the Army for at least 10 years. 2. Children of APS personnel classified as Ex-serviceman as per Govt. of India, Ministry of Defense, letter No 9 (52)/88/D(Res) dated 19 Jul 89. 3. Children of APS personnel who are on deputation and who have put in 10 years of service in the Army. 4. Children of APS personnel who are directly recruited into APS & completed 10 years of service and who as per their terms and conditions of service, retired from APS without reversion to P&T Department after completing their minimum pensionable service of which 10 years was in the Army. 5. Children of members of MNS who have 10 years service as regular members of MNS or are in receipt of pension from the Army. 6. Children of TA personnel who have completed 10 years of embodied service. Children of Air Force, Navy and Paramilitary forces like CRPF, BSF, ITBP, CISF, Assam Rifles, GREF and DSC are not eligible

Delhi State Candidates. Delhi XI and XII


OBC-DEF/OPEN-DEF/SC-DEF/ST-DEF


Delhi State Candidates. Delhi XI and XII and DEFENCE CRITERIA (As per Defence Criteria)


  1. Priority I : Widows/Wards of Defence personnel/Para Military Personnel killed in action

  2. Priority II : Wards of Defence Personnel and ex-servicemen disabled in action and boarded out from service with disability attributed to military service.

  3. Priority III : Widows/Wards of Defence personnel/Para Military personnel who died in peace time with death attributable to military service.

  4. Priority IV : Wards of Defence personnel/Para Military personnel disabled in service and boarded out from service with disability attributable to military service.

  5. Priority V : Wards of serving Defence personnel and Ex receipt of Gallantry Awards.


    1. Param Vir Chakra

    2. Ashok Chakra

    3. Maha Vir Chakra

    4. Kirti Chakra

    5. Vir Chakra

    6. Shaurya Chakra

    7. Sena, Nau Sena, Vayu Sena Medal

    8. Mention in Despatches

    9. Presidentâ€™s Police Medal for Gallantry

    10. Police Medal for Gallantry



  6. Priority VI : Wards of Ex-Servicemen. Required Certificate: Original ex book supported by PPO (Pension Payment Order).



  7. Priority VII : Wives of


    1. Defence personnel disabled in action and boarded out from service.

    2. Defence personnel disabled in service and boarded out with disability attributable to militaryservice.

    3. Ex-Servicemen and serving personnel who are in receipt of Gallantry Awards.



  8. Priority VIII : Wards of Serving Personnel.



  9. Priority IX : Wives of Serving Personnel.
